Akdal MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun is the new product from Turkish company Akdal Arms. This weapon is intended for civilian and security use, and mimics the famous M16 rifle in its layout and placement of most controls. It is remarkably light for its caliber and size, because of extensive use of modern, high strength plastics.

Akdal MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun utilizes conventional gas-operated action with annual (ring-type) gas piston, which is located around the support tube that runs below the barrel. Return spring is also located around the same tube, which is concealed by enlarged polymer handguards. Barrel is quick-removable from upper receiver, barrel locking is achieved by tilting locking piece inside the bolt, which engages the barrel extension. Charging handle is attached to the bolt and projects on the right side of the receiver. The upper receiver is manufactured from aluminum alloy; lower receiver, along with pistol grip and shoulder stock, is manufactured as one piece from impact-resistant polymer. Akdal MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun utilizes detachable box magazines, each holding 5 rounds; an M16-style bolt stop and bolt release button are incorporated into the lower receiver. Manual safety also duplicates M16-style, being located on the left side of the receiver, above the pistol grip. Standard sights include front post, installed on the M16-style removable base, and a detachable M16A2-style carrying handle with built-in diopter sight. postcontent:
I have 3 brand new 22rd Glock 22 .40cal mags for trade. I loaded 1 of these twice the other two have never had a round in them. I will also throw in a nice $35 used black tri mag pouch that holds them great. $50 bucks each, $150 for all three and the mag pouch. I will only trade these as a package deal. I would like to trade these for a cheap gun that works. Eaa/Rossi .38, .357, 12/20 gauge shotgun, Mosin Nagant,  Mil surplus rifle or handgun, .22, Black powder gun. Ammo 762x39, 762x54r, 9mm, .40cal. I don't mind old guns but anything I trade for must be in working condition. I am not marking up these mags and playing the fear game. I am not paying these fear base prices either if you have ammo I paid $135 + tax at Tanner in Sept for 500rds of 762x39 and thats what I plan on tradeing for today. I am not going to screw you and I expect the same. Stop paying these fear based prices it will only hurt us all in the long run. Let your local gun store know that it is messed up for them to cash in on our fear. They are not paying one dime more for thier stuff and everything has gone up. Trade only, not for sale unless you want to pay $300 cash, If anyone going to get some crazy ass marked up price for these it's going to be me.

 All I hear from local gun store owners is how bad they need are help. Don't buy ammo from Wal-mart we can't compete with thier prices. Big box stores are killing the little guy. So I help, I buy ammo from the gun store and buy in bulk from the gun show and try to support the little guy. Now for the second time in four years These assholes are cashing in on are fear. Seems like everything jumped 30% when Oboma got into office and nothing happened and prices never went back down. Now it's happening again. Every chance they get these guy's screw us and I think it's pretty jack up of them. Wal-mart didn't double there prices, I think we should all stop playing along. If your gun store raises prices shop somewhere else, or better yet we should stop buying all together for 60-90 days a let them snap back to reality. I will not let them keep scewing me for the rest of my life and niether should you. What ever happens is going to happen if we let them set the bar this high by paying these crazy prices then we will be paying them for ever.

P.S. I will not trade these to anyone I think  is going to try and re-sell them for a profit, fuck that and shame on you.
